title: KennDog On Hate From LA Rappers, Turning Out a Stud, Streets of Watts, & More
description:
KennDog talks about his come-up, his hit records, signing with a label, going viral on Tiktok and more!

-----
00:00 Intro
4:07 - Seeing his first body not too long ago
8:14 - Used to be short and fat like Flakko, playing sports when younger, running track making him taller
13:48 - Complementing Gina on her style, going from basketball to music
16:12 - Having a job as a janitor before music, dropping car freestyle video on Facebook and it doing crazy numbers
18:19 - Turning out “stud” that looked like Jada Pinkett
24:07 - “Catch this vibe” song doing 100k on SoundCloud
26:21 - Living with his pops and him not believing in the music, getting a job at the $1 store, being fired because an employee of 19 years ratted him out for stealing
29:38 - Becoming a mobile barber during the pandemic, making $400-500 a day
33:25 - Living with his aunt when song went viral, Charli D’Amelio doing tik tok
36:05 - Signing with Warner records for 9 months, getting out the deal and dropping the hit “Beethoven”
38:18 - Used to be a big Kendrick, YG fan back in the day
42:43 - Only having 7 songs out right now 3 of them being massive hits, signing to another label
47:25 - Introducing his team, them realizing he was special, Kenndog loving the fans, new music dropping
49:15 - Setting the record straight that LA needs to get behind Kenndog
